issue.body:
Using EF Core 8.0 with Npgsql 8.0
Postgres 15.3

The minimal sample repro code:

```csharp
var tags = new List<string> { "drama" };
var records = dbContext.Books
    .Include(e => e.Metadata)
    .ThenInclude(e => e.Tags)
    .Where(e => tags.All(t => e.Metadata.Tags.Select(b => b.Tag).Contains(t)))
    .ToList();

public class Book
{
  public int Id { get; set; }
  public BookMetadata Metadata { get; set; }
}

public class BookMetadata
{
  public int Id { get; set; }
  public List<BookTag> Tags { get; set; }
}

public class BookTag
{
      public int Id { get; set; }
      public string Tag { get; set; }
}
```

Fails with:
```
  Exception data:
    Severity: ERROR
    SqlState: 42703
    MessageText: column t.value does not exist
    Position: 755
    File: parse_relation.c
    Line: 3656
    Routine: errorMissingColumn Npgsql.PostgresException (0x80004005): 42703: column t.value does not exist
```

Workaround: use SingleQuery

```csharp
var tags = new List<string> { "drama" };
var records = dbContext.Books
    .AsSingleQuery()
    .Include(e => e.Metadata)
    .ThenInclude(e => e.Tags)
    .Where(e => tags.All(t => e.Metadata.Tags.Select(b => b.Tag).Contains(t)))
    .ToList();
```
